What's there to say about Starbucks that hasn't already been said? Aside from being debatably overpriced, I have nothing bad to say about the chain or this particular location.  I typically drink my coffee black at home, but when I go to Starbucks for my fix I oscillate between this, something a little more exotic like a nitro cold brew with some heavy cream and cold foam or a caramel macchiato and the caffeinated milkshakes known as Frappuccinos. A simple iced green tea with honey or one of the Refreshers are also a good choice if you want something other than coffee.  If I'm hungry, they have great options for a light meal, some of my favorites being the spinach, feta and egg white sandwich or any variety of the sous vide egg bites. Any of their pastries are a good choice if you want to indulge your sweet tooth.  All of the food choices at Starbucks are markedly higher quality than comparable options at, say, a 7-11, and the chain is almost as prevalent, so if you want to treat your taste buds kindly while on the go you can't go wrong here.

I made the mistake of getting some coffee and planning to do some work in too close a proximity to the dismissal time at the school. What was a nice, peaceful environment turned into school recess. Endless numbers of high school children acting as high school children will act.  Please note that I do not blame the kids ask kids will act as kids will act. I question if this particular Starbucks gets enough revenue to warrant what is surely a daily invasion.  I will probably come back to the Starbucks but I will certainly never darken its doors in the mid-afternoon. I would advise any reader to heed this advice.
